  "text": "These definitions can be applied to the wide range of different dynamical responses [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . They do not require that the signal eventually returns to its initial steady state, and they are also suitable for oscillatory transitions. Numerically calculated steady states were used as initial conditions to simulate the continuous dynamics of model species over time to the final time point of 630 min.",
